simple_means.memory_skill: ex 出 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 拔出刺 → 灭绝的，注意：ex后接s开头的词根时省略s

tr: being out or having grown cold
example: threw his extinct cigarette into the stream

tr: lost or especially having died out leaving no living representatives

value.def: A species of animal or plant that is extinct no longer has any living members, either in the world or in a particular place.

example.ex: It is 250 years since the wolf became extinct in Britain.
example.tran: 狼在英国已经灭绝250年了。

value.def: If a particular kind of worker, way of life, or type of activity is extinct, it no longer exists, because of changes in society.

example.ex: If the current trend continues, black farmers in the United States may be extinct by the end of this decade...
example.tran: 如果当前趋势继续发展下去，美国的黑人农民将在这个十年末不复存在。

example.ex: Herbalism had become an all but extinct skill in the Western world.
example.tran: 草药医术在西方已经成了一门几乎绝迹的技艺。

value.tran: （某类劳动者、生活方式或活动）不复存在的，废除了的

value.def: An extinct volcano is one that does not erupt or is not expected to erupt any more.

example.ex: Its tallest volcano, long extinct, is Olympus Mons.
example.tran: 它最高的火山是早已熄灭的奥林波斯山。

partsOfSpeech.dec: dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 把刺分开后显得清楚的；明显的 → 清楚的；明显的
dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ion，distinct 的名词 → 区别；优秀
dis 分开 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ive …的 → 有区别的；与众不同的
di〔s〕分离 + stingu 刺；刺激 + ish 使… → 把不同的刺分离 → 区别
distinguish 区别；辨出 + ed 表形容词 → 与众不同的 → 著名的
ex 出 + tinct〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 → 拔出刺 → 灭绝的，注意：ex后接s开头的词根时省略s
extinct 灭绝的 + ion 表名词 → 灭绝
ex 出 + tingu 刺 + ish 使… → 把刺拔出，刺引申为火焰 → 熄灭
in 使… + stig〔= stinct〕刺；刺激 + ate 做，造成，使… → 刺激〔别人〕→ 煽动
in 向内 + stinct 刺；刺激 → 内在的刺激 → 本能
stimul 刺；刺激 + ate 做，造成，使… → 刺激，鼓励
stimul 刺；刺激 + ation 行为，过程，状态，结果 → 刺激，鼓励
sting 刺；刺激 + y …的 → 对钱的事挑刺 → 小气的
